(If anyone wonders why Chordate suddenly forgot about the intruder, it's 
because I'm trying to buy Shadowarrior time to respond, since she hasn't yet, 
and he's a little amazed at Feline)

Chordate:



Chordate's optics went wide when Feline took his arm.  He looked around to 
see if anyone else was there.  "The mess hall?" he checked his internal 
chronometer.  That intruder wasn't going anywhere, and if it did, the 
intruder wasn't worth bothering with.

He was about to gather his senses, but lost them once more when he felt 
Feline's soft furred tail rubbing up against his neck.  He regained his 
senses after a few seconds, smiling to Feline.  "The mess hall...this way." 
he said, walking down a corridor for the mess hall, but slow enough so that 
she could hold on and keep up.
